main event: A civilian airline passenger photographed an elliptical object with tiny perforations in the sky while flying between Coos Bay and Portland, Oregon on September 6, 1956.
interesting points: The object was photographed at an altitude of 27,000 feet and was described as a 'space ship,' The passenger requested information from the U.S. Air Force regarding any aircraft in the area at that time, Analysis of the photo suggested it might be an emulsion flaw or a developing error, The U.S. Air Force reported no other sightings or aircraft in the area at the time, The passenger used a Brownie camera, which had limitations that could result in blurred images.
location: Between Coos Bay & Portland, Oregon, USA
